"n./v.接触；互通信息 【英】 n./v. 接触(touching);互通信息(communicat ing) 【记】 con(共同)+tact(接触 ) →共同接触 【同】 同根词: intact(原封不动的); tactile(触觉的) n. = v 接触 = touching; 相互联系 = communicating 【记】con共同, tact接触－共同接触 【参】intact(adj 完整无缺的; 童贞的; 未阉的); tactile(adj 触觉的) 【记】con 共同 + tact 接触→共同接触；con + touch → it, touch的ou发a音 contact (v.)  1834, ""put in contact,"" from contact (n.). Meaning ""get in touch with"" is 1927, American English. Related: Contacted; contacting. contact (n.)  1620s, ""action of touching,"" from Latin contactus ""a touching,"" from past participle of contingere ""to touch, seize,"" from com- ""together"" (see com-) + tangere ""to touch"" (see tangent (adj.)). Figurative sense of ""connection, communication"" is from 1818. As a signal to the person about to spin an aircraft propeller that the ignition is switched on, the word was in use by 1913. Contact lens is first recorded 1888; short form contact is from 1961."
